						               													<description>Arms &amp;amp; Influence is a political strategy card game that puts you and 3 others in a contest to build the world&amp;rsquo;s most dominant power. Players build a social pyramid and attempt to advance their society to prominence by achieving 7 Victory Points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, players choose a total of 2 cards from the Society or Action deck. The Society deck consists of Leaders and Populations; the Action deck has everything else: Advancements, Competitions and Actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once they select their cards, they must take 2 actions. Using a card consists of a turn. If they cannot make a move, they must discard as an action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With populations, players build their social pyramid in an attempt to have 5 populations. Once achieved they can elect a leader.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each population gives players one of 4 resources: Military Strength, Equality, Espionage, and Production.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;They then use these resources to obtain Advancements such as &amp;quot;Man on Mars&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Nuclear Submarine&amp;quot; etc. (worth one Victory Point). Each which require a combination of 4 resources shown on the card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players strategically modify their pyramid, elect new leaders, to obtain new Advancements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition to Advancements, players can earn victory points by winning a Competition. When a competition is played, players compete to have the most resource of a given type by the end of the turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The road to victory will not be easy, as players will use Action cards to disrupt each other's rise to power.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to 7 Victory Points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
